-- Now this is the CAST clause practice query, The CAST clause is used to convert a value from one data type to another.

SELECT CAST (Order_Date AS DATE)
 FROM
  superstore.superstore_sales_data;
  /* This query retrieves the Order_Date from the superstore_sales_data table and uses the CAST function to convert it 
    to a DATE data type.
  This is useful when you want to ensure that the Order_Date is treated as a date value */

-- Now, their are mainly 5 data types in SQL, which are as follows:
-- INT, DECIMAL, CHAR, DATE, DATETIME, and we can use the CAST function to convert values between these data types as needed.

